OL,3,CChildren to be taught how to spot fake
OL,4,Cnews and 'putrid' conspiracy theories
OL,6,FPupils might analyse newspaper
OL,7,Farticles in English lessons in a way
OL,8,Fthat would help weed out fabricated
OL,9,Fclickbait from true reporting.
OL,11,FIn computer lessons, they could be
OL,12,Ftaught how to spot fake news sites and
OL,13,Fmaths lessons could include analysing
OL,14,Fstatistics in context.
OL,16,FMs Phillipson told The Telegraph:
OL,17,F"It's more important than ever that we
OL,18,Fgive young people the knowledge and
OL,19,Fskills to be able to challenge what
OL,20,Fthey see online.
